error: Server: Bind failed

Bind failed error is returned by a Unix system call, specifically by the bind() function. 
This error typically occurs because the previous instance of the server didn’t fully release 
the port (8080 in your case), which can happen if you exit with Ctrl+C. 
When the server process is terminated abruptly, the operating system may not immediately 
release the bound port, leaving it in a "TIME_WAIT" state.

Wait for the Port to Be Released: After using Ctrl+C, wait a few seconds before 
restarting the server, as the OS will eventually release the port from the TIME_WAIT state.

or

> kill -9 $(lsof -t i:8081)
